---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="L1 Help Desk — Build Crystal"
  description="A Crystal L1 help desk worker clears the ticket queue overnight, handles password resets and common L1 tickets, and escalates what it can't close. ~$2,500/mo. Ready in 3-5 days."
  active="workers"
>
  <article class="worker">
    <div class="frame">
      <header class="worker-head">
        <p class="eyebrow">Available for hire</p>
        <h1>L1 Help Desk.</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          A virtual employee for your ticket queue. Works overnights and weekends, handles password resets and common
          L1 work, closes what it can close, and routes what it can't to L2 with clean notes.
        </p>
        <div class="head-meta">
          <div><strong>~$2,500 / mo</strong><span>~50% of the human hire</span></div>
          <div><strong>24 / 7</strong><span>queue coverage, no SLA gaps</span></div>
          <div><strong>3&ndash;5 days</strong><span>from call to live</span></div>
          <div><strong>28 days</strong><span>free pilot</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="head-ctas">
          <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-primary" data-hire data-role="l1-helpdesk">Hire L1 help desk</a>
          <a href="#details" class="btn btn-secondary">See what it does</a>
        </div>
      </header>

      <section class="worker-section" id="details">
        <h2>What a Crystal L1 worker does.</h2>
        <ul class="does">
          <li>Works the ticket queue overnight, weekends, and holidays.</li>
          <li>Handles password resets, MFA resets, access requests, and common L1 tickets.</li>
          <li>Closes what it can close. Routes what it can't, with notes for the L2 picking it up.</li>
          <li>Escalates out-of-scope tickets to a named engineer with context.</li>
          <li>Every correction sticks &mdash; the same ticket doesn't stump it twice.</li>
          <li>0 SLA breaches overnight becomes a realistic goal, not a wishlist item.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="worker-section">
        <h2>What it doesn't do.</h2>
        <p>
          Anything requiring on-site hands &mdash; hardware swaps, cable runs, physical presence. Anything outside
          the scope you define at setup; we're upfront about the line and the worker is scoped to respect it.
          Anything customer-facing before you're ready &mdash; most L1 deployments start internal-only, with tickets
          from your staff, not your end customers, until you're confident.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="worker-section">
        <h2>For MSPs and internal IT.</h2>
        <p>
          If you're running an MSP or internal IT team and your L2 is getting paged for L1 tickets at 11 PM, this is
          the shape of the fix. The worker closes the routine stuff, leaves a clean handoff on anything that needs
          judgment, and never calls in sick the Monday after a long weekend.
        </p>
        <p>
          On the technical side: it's a Claude-based worker scoped to tier-1. Defined tools, defined escalation rules.
          Integrations with ConnectWise and Autotask today &mdash; Halo and NinjaRMM on the roadmap. If yours isn't on
          the list, we build the connector or we don't take the deal. Formal compliance certifications
          (SOC 2, ISO 27001) &mdash; we don't have them yet. If you need one to buy, tell us which and we'll talk about
          whether it's realistic.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="worker-section">
        <h2>The math.</h2>
        <table class="math-table">
          <tbody>
            <tr><th>Market salary (loaded)</th><td>~$60,000 / yr</td></tr>
            <tr><th>Crystal L1 worker</th><td>~$2,500 / mo</td></tr>
            <tr><th>Coverage</th><td>24 / 7 (including overnights & weekends)</td></tr>
            <tr><th>Setup time</th><td>3&ndash;5 business days</td></tr>
            <tr><th>Free trial</th><td>28 days, no card</td></tr>
            <tr><th>Included</th><td>Worker, build-out, training, integrations, ongoing corrections, maintenance, updates.</td></tr>
            <tr><th>Not included</th><td>Your Anthropic API bill &mdash; you own the account, we don't resell it.</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <section class="worker-section">
        <h2>The honest part.</h2>
        <p>
          Day one is rough, like any new L1 hire &mdash; it doesn't know your tools or your end users yet. Corrections
          go into the worker's knowledge base and stick; drift is a real problem and we monitor for it. You keep a
          kill switch. Nothing customer-facing goes out without you being able to reverse it.
        </p>
      </section>

      <div class="worker-cta">
        <h3>Hiring L1 help desk?</h3>
        <p>Book a 15-minute working session. We'll walk through your current queue and show you what one of ours would do with it.</p>
        <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-primary" data-hire data-role="l1-helpdesk">Book a working session</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .worker { padding: clamp(3rem, 7vw, 5rem) 0 clamp(3rem, 6vw, 4rem); }
  .worker-head { max-width: 56rem; margin-bottom: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem); }
  .eyebrow {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }
  .worker-head h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 4.8vw, 3.5rem);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }
  .worker-head .lede {
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1.6vw, 1.2rem);
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    max-width: 52ch;
    margin: 0 0 1.75rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .head-meta {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(10rem, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: 1.25rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .head-meta strong {
    display: block;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--ink);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .head-meta span {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
  }
  .head-ctas { display: flex; gap: 0.6rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }

  .worker-section {
    padding: 2rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    max-width: 56rem;
  }
  .worker-section h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 2.4vw, 1.8rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }
  .worker-section p {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    max-width: 62ch;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .worker-section p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .does {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.7rem;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    font-size: 1.02rem;
    max-width: 62ch;
  }
  .does li {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 0.7rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .does li::before {
    content: "";
    width: 5px; height: 5px;
    background: var(--accent);
    border-radius: 50%;
    margin-top: 0.65em;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .math-table {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 56rem;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
  .math-table th, .math-table td {
    text-align: left;
    padding: 0.75rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    vertical-align: top;
  }
  .math-table th {
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    width: 32%;
  }
  .math-table td { color: var(--ink); }

  .worker-cta {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    padding: 2rem 2.25rem;
    background: var(--accent-wash);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    max-width: 56rem;
  }
  .worker-cta h3 { margin: 0 0 0.4rem; font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; }
  .worker-cta p { margin: 0 0 1rem; color: var(--ink-2); }
</style>
